{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/the-odin-project/top-learn-arrays-and-loops/learn-arrays-and-loops-lesson-f","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"top-learn-arrays-and-loops","challengeType":15,"description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Petlja <code>for</code> je drugi tip petlje koji se koristi za izvršavanje bloka koda više puta. Petlja <code>for</code> se koristi kada je poznat broj iteracija. Sintaksa petlje <code>for</code> je sledeća:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">for (initialization; condition; increment/decrement) {\n  // code block to be executed\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Na primer, deo koda ispod ispisuje brojeve od 1 do 5:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">for (let i = 1; i &#x3C;= 5; i++) {\n  console.log(i);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Da biste iterirali preko niza podataka koristeći petlju <code>for</code>, možete koristiti svojstvo dužine tog niza. Na primer, kodni isječak ispod štampa elemente niza podataka:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">const arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];\nfor (let i = 0; i &#x3C; arr.length; i++) {\n  console.log(arr[i]);\n}\n</code></pre>\n</section>","nodules":null,"explanation":null,"helpCategory":"Odin","instructions":"","fields":{"slug":"/learn/the-odin-project/top-learn-arrays-and-loops/learn-arrays-and-loops-lesson-f"},"questions":[{"text":"<p>Šta će biti rezultat ovog fragmenta koda JavaScript ispod?</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">const items = ['apple', 'banana', 'cherry', 'date'];\nfor (let i = 1; i &#x3C; items.length; i++) {\n  console.log(items[i]);\n}\n</code></pre>","answers":[{"answer":"<pre><code class=\"language-md\">apple\nbanana\ncherry\ndate\n</code></pre>","feedback":null,"audioId":null},{"answer":"<pre><code class=\"language-md\">banana\ncherry\n</code></pre>","feedback":null,"audioId":null},{"answer":"<pre><code class=\"language-md\">apple\nbanana\